# Project-Specific Development Rules

## Section Title Component Usage

- **ALWAYS** use the `SectionTitle` component from `@/components/ui/section-title` for all new sections
- Import: `import { SectionTitle } from "@/components/ui/section-title"`
- Use appropriate variants: `"center"`, `"start"`, or `"start-dark"` based on design requirements
- Configure props as needed: `showDivider`, `showLogo`, `className`, etc.

## UI Components Usage

- **ALWAYS** use components from `@/components/ui/` directory
- Available components: `Button`, `Card`, `Accordion`, `Tabs`, `Carousel`, `Form`, `Label`, `AnimatedButton`
- Import pattern: `import { ComponentName } from "@/components/ui/component-name"`
- Never create custom UI components when equivalent exists in `@/components/ui/`

## Content Management

- **ALWAYS** use content from `@/content.ts` file
- Import: `import content from "@/content.ts"`
- Access content using the structured object: `content.sectionName.propertyName`
- Never hardcode text content - always reference from `content.ts`
- Add new content sections to `content.ts` when creating new features

## Design System and Styling

- **ALWAYS** use Tailwind CSS classes from the design system defined in `@/app/globals.css`
- Use CSS custom properties: `--color-primary`, `--color-secondary`, `--color-foreground`, etc.
- Apply typography classes: `text-4xl`, `text-3xl`, `text-2xl`, etc. as defined in the base layer
- Use spacing utilities: `space-y-4`, `space-x-4`, `p-4`, `m-4`, etc.
- Follow responsive design patterns: `lg:text-3xl`, `md:px-6`, etc.
- Use container class: `container` (defined in globals.css with max-width and padding)

## Color System

- Primary: `#021a60` (--primary)
- Primary Light: `#032da6` (--primary-light)
- Secondary: `#f25b06` (--secondary)
- Background: `#fafbfd` (--background)
- Foreground: `#333333` (--foreground)
- Use CSS custom properties instead of hardcoded hex values

## Typography

- Use the Lama Sans font family as defined in globals.css
- Apply heading styles: `h1`, `h2`, `h3`, `h4`, `h5`, `h6` with predefined classes
- Use body text styling: `p`, `small` with appropriate classes
- Follow the typography hierarchy defined in the base layer

## Component Structure

- Create new sections in `@/components/sections/` directory
- Use lowercase with dashes for file names: `new-section.tsx`
- Export as named exports: `export function NewSection() {}`
- Follow the established pattern of other section components

## Example Implementation

```tsx
import { SectionTitle } from "@/components/ui/section-title";
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import content from "@/content.ts";

export function NewSection() {
  return (
    <section className="py-16 bg-background">
      <div className="container">
        <SectionTitle variant="center">{content.newSection.title}</SectionTitle>

        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-8">
          {content.newSection.items.map((item, index) => (
            <Card key={index} className="p-6">
              <h3 className="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4">
                {item.title}
              </h3>
              <p className="text-muted-foreground mb-4">{item.description}</p>
              <Button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
                {item.buttonText}
              </Button>
            </Card>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

## Prohibited Practices

- ❌ Hardcoding text content in components
- ❌ Creating custom UI components when existing ones are available
- ❌ Using hardcoded color values instead of CSS custom properties
- ❌ Creating sections without using SectionTitle component
- ❌ Using inline styles instead of Tailwind classes
- ❌ Not following the established file structure and naming conventions
